The paper discusses the use of data mining and predictive models for improving students' performance in higher education. This falls under the domain of educational data mining, which is a subfield of machine learning and data mining. The paper specifically uses a classification model (Byes classification) to predict the performance of students. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
